notesStmt.note: This meeting constitutes an internal staff meeting of [org15], which is a forwarding agency and a daughter firm of [org11]. S1, S3, S4, S5, and S7 are all employees of [org15] and participate in the meeting. S1 is the senior employee and the head of the team and therefore he also chairs the meeting. Immediately before this internal meeting, a sales meeting with a representative from an airline, [org2], took place. Some of the comments at the beginning of the meeting refer to this preceding meeting, the airline [org2] and the sales representative who has just left. Subsequently, the main topics of the meeting are internal organizational matters relating to staff changes, vacation times and business contacts.

namespace.tagUsage: Used to mark a stretch of speech commonly preceded and followed by a pause or by a change of speaker. Auis, however, not required to be bounded by a pause or a change of speaker, nor does it represent a turn in a conversation analytic sense. At a minimum, auis some phonetic production or noise made by a given speaker or a group of speakers.
